			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:15:32',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '53',
			'name' => 'Fort Tyrisen',
			'description' => 'One of the old fortresses of the White Order, long abandoned. It sits in the remote northern wilderness of Batyrun, inspiring many tales of ghosts and lost souls.',
			'parent_id' => '21',
			'lft' => '28',
			'rght' => '29',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 06:26:25',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:26:25',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '54',
			'name' => 'Ikadean Isles',
			'description' => 'A group of inhabited islands between North and South Tasif. Ikadeans live in its pleasant towns. Though The Guards claim ownership of these islands, the people there consider themselves separate.',
			'parent_id' => '4',
			'lft' => '49',
			'rght' => '52',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 06:30:29',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:31:17',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '55',
			'name' => 'Beleria',
			'description' => 'The largest city on the Ikadean Islands. Almost everybody who travels here seeks a simple and peaceful life in this beautiful place. ',
			'parent_id' => '54',
			'lft' => '50',
			'rght' => '51',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 06:34:19',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:34:19',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '56',
			'name' => 'Rudon',
			'description' => 'A small city in northern Pitae Desert. Rudon mostly deals with trading with the people of the desert. ',
			'parent_id' => '45',
			'lft' => '68',
			'rght' => '69',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 06:37:38',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:41:09',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '57',
			'name' => 'Enena',
			'description' => 'A small bandit city deep in Pitae Desert. It acts as a type of desert crossroad area for travellers and traders.',
			'parent_id' => '45',
			'lft' => '70',
			'rght' => '71',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 06:41:01',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:41:01',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '58',
			'name' => 'Agurin',
			'description' => 'A bandit port city towards the south. It is the most common way for people to travel eastward to the desert island of Tekrikri. ',
			'parent_id' => '45',
			'lft' => '72',
			'rght' => '73',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 06:41:56',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:41:56',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '59',
			'name' => 'Kartara',
			'description' => 'A large, sacred, ancient city deep in the Sacred Heder desert. Katrekri live here and they do not welcome strangers or foreigners. It is said that Katrekri are experts at fire and earth magic. ',
			'parent_id' => '7',
			'lft' => '105',
			'rght' => '106',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 06:45:49',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:45:49',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '60',
			'name' => 'Weder Forest',
			'description' => 'Ketrem\'s strange forests. It is a common quest for adventurers to travel into these woods and discover the people rumoured to be living inside, but nobody seems to be able to find any signs of civilisation. ',
			'parent_id' => '8',
			'lft' => '109',
			'rght' => '110',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 06:47:52',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:47:52',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '61',
			'name' => 'Windaeser',
			'description' => 'One of the main provinces of Huirnon, boasting a capital city and good forests amidst all the cold tundra. Passage to the eastern half of Huirnon requires one to pass through Alacas at the very eastern point of Windaeser. ',
			'parent_id' => '9',
			'lft' => '113',
			'rght' => '122',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 06:55:06',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:57:39',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '62',
			'name' => 'Maharaba',
			'description' => 'The southwestern province of Huirnon which contains its most popular port. Maharaba is mostly cold fields but the Dunin Mountains protect it from the harshness to the north. ',
			'parent_id' => '9',
			'lft' => '123',
			'rght' => '128',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 06:59:04',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 06:59:04',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '63',
			'name' => 'Cenarta',
			'description' => 'The central province of western Huirnon. Cenarta is mostly a huge valley filled with rivers; mountains to the west and north force most travellers along its central main road. ',
			'parent_id' => '9',
			'lft' => '129',
			'rght' => '140',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:00:40',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:00:40',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '64',
			'name' => 'Rennisc',
			'description' => 'One of the coldest human provinces in Riiga, Rennisc consists of the northern shores and it boasts a huge freshwater lake and fantastic fishing in Kapua Bay. ',
			'parent_id' => '9',
			'lft' => '141',
			'rght' => '146',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:02:08',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:02:08',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '65',
			'name' => 'Stelake',
			'description' => 'A small province to the west through which many pass. Stelake has several large lakes with unique fish in them. Most of the towns there make good business on these fish. ',
			'parent_id' => '9',
			'lft' => '147',
			'rght' => '152',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:03:33',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:03:33',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '66',
			'name' => 'ALACAS',
			'description' => 'The capital of Huirnon, Alacas is a city build over the water and is only possible thanks to the genius of generations of water mages who live there. It is a city of wondrous architecture and intellectual greatness. ',
			'parent_id' => '61',
			'lft' => '114',
			'rght' => '115',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:05:00',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:05:00',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '67',
			'name' => 'Gama',
			'description' => 'A busy city in the middle of the land situated beside Rielle Lake and Riellewood. Good resources have contributed to the ongoing survival of Gama and its popular markets are testimony to this. ',
			'parent_id' => '61',
			'lft' => '116',
			'rght' => '117',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:10:04',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:12:16',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '68',
			'name' => 'Mekahn',
			'description' => 'This old city is littered with castles from the White Order\'s time. It overlooks a lake called Dunin\'s Tears and acts as a major checkpoint along Huirnon\'s main roads. ',
			'parent_id' => '63',
			'lft' => '130',
			'rght' => '131',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:12:05',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:12:05',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '69',
			'name' => 'Herakhor',
			'description' => 'A small city on the Rielle River. It supplies many surrounding towns with wood from the good forests to the south. ',
			'parent_id' => '61',
			'lft' => '118',
			'rght' => '119',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:14:00',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:14:00',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '70',
			'name' => 'Makeran',
			'description' => 'This small city, along with Ellecil, is one of the only places to gather fish from Kapua Bay. ',
			'parent_id' => '61',
			'lft' => '120',
			'rght' => '121',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:15:02',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:15:02',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '71',
			'name' => 'Tassina',
			'description' => 'A large port town on the southern shore. Tassina is the fastest and easiest way to reach Progora Island to the south. Due to a conflict in the past, this city is strictly unreligious. ',
			'parent_id' => '63',
			'lft' => '132',
			'rght' => '133',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:17:17',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:17:17',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '72',
			'name' => 'Diesily',
			'description' => 'A small mining city just south of Ellecilar Mountains and on the Diesil River. It is a relatively quiet and humble city. ',
			'parent_id' => '63',
			'lft' => '134',
			'rght' => '135',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:18:16',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:18:16',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '73',
			'name' => 'Teskin',
			'description' => 'A small mining city northeast of Diesily. Teskin is colder and quieter on the surface; many homes are built underground in old mines so that people can save warmth in the smaller spaces.',
			'parent_id' => '63',
			'lft' => '136',
			'rght' => '137',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:19:39',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:19:39',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '74',
			'name' => 'Tyson',
			'description' => 'A small city high in the Dunin Mountains. Tyson was once an outpost for the White Order, but The Guards had it torn down as it was apparently an eyesore to all the lands it overlooked. ',
			'parent_id' => '63',
			'lft' => '138',
			'rght' => '139',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:34:58',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:34:58',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '75',
			'name' => 'Ellecil',
			'description' => 'An old, beautiful city, further north than any other in Riiga. Its high stone walls keep out most of the cold and it is dotted with warm taverns and enclosed public walkways. Ellecil\'s port is filled with some of the toughest fishermen around.',
			'parent_id' => '64',
			'lft' => '142',
			'rght' => '143',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:37:51',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:37:51',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '76',
			'name' => 'Charon Forest',
			'description' => 'This vast, icy forest is believed to be the hiding place of Ashmah Gvoranshun, one of The Enemy\'s war generals. Thus, it is considered, not only uninhabitable, but also extremely dangerous. ',
			'parent_id' => '64',
			'lft' => '144',
			'rght' => '145',
			'created' => '2010-07-31 07:41:35',
			'modified' => '2010-07-31 07:41:35',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '77',
			'name' => 'Harasinar',
			'description' => 'A small city south of the famous lakes of Stelake. There was once another lake just west of Harasinar, but it has since dried up. ',
			'parent_id' => '65',
			'lft' => '148',
			'rght' => '149',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 07:40:05',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 07:40:05',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '78',
			'name' => 'Mael\'s Woods',
			'description' => 'A steep and icy evergreen forest. Mael\'s Woods are home to countless self-proclaimed marauder lords and master assassins. ',
			'parent_id' => '65',
			'lft' => '150',
			'rght' => '151',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 07:44:25',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 07:44:25',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '79',
			'name' => 'Ubura',
			'description' => 'A large, strangely empty city. Ubura is somewhat unique in that its family of governers are descended from generations of eccentric inventors. It is a city of creation, construction, and bizarre architecture. Its residents appear to want to stay indoors.',
			'parent_id' => '62',
			'lft' => '124',
			'rght' => '125',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 07:46:17',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 07:46:17',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '80',
			'name' => 'Diaja',
			'description' => 'A small city on the southern side of South Salloten river, known for its grand old bridge leading over the river.',
			'parent_id' => '62',
			'lft' => '126',
			'rght' => '127',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 07:48:15',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 07:48:15',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '81',
			'name' => 'Minteret',
			'description' => 'A vast, open province consisting mostly of rocky tundra and scattered open woods. Its northern border is marked by the White River, and crossing its waters leads one into Sirin territory. ',
			'parent_id' => '10',
			'lft' => '155',
			'rght' => '164',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 07:50:56',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 07:50:56',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '82',
			'name' => 'Velenaia',
			'description' => 'A large province consisting mostly of the treacherous Sideways Mountains. Towns are scattered around the western and southern shores. ',
			'parent_id' => '10',
			'lft' => '165',
			'rght' => '172',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 07:53:01',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 07:53:01',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '83',
			'name' => 'Taroiccin',
			'description' => 'One of the warmest provinces in Huirnon, thanks to the shield and filter that the huge Vastin Forest provides. Though far from the Sideways Mountains, many rich families in Taroiccin own mining guilds far to the west. ',
			'parent_id' => '10',
			'lft' => '173',
			'rght' => '184',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 07:54:35',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 07:54:35',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '84',
			'name' => 'Sirinuirnon',
			'description' => 'Encased in snow and ice almost the whole year round, Sirinuirnon is inhabited by Sirins. The Qari Mountains to the north are the furthest north any human can get. ',
			'parent_id' => '10',
			'lft' => '185',
			'rght' => '188',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 07:57:52',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 07:58:11',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '85',
			'name' => 'Progora Island',
			'description' => 'A large island where progorens can be found. Though it lies in a northern sea, the sun is surprisingly strong there, and its larger inhabited islands are somewhat pleasant in terms of weather. ',
			'parent_id' => '10',
			'lft' => '189',
			'rght' => '192',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:02:04',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:02:04',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '86',
			'name' => 'Cepriken',
			'description' => 'Progora Island\'s largest town. Tall, open buildings welcome the sunlight and ocean breeze and countless farmers sell their island produce across the sea to make business. The Guards rule here, but the progorens do not like them. ',
			'parent_id' => '85',
			'lft' => '190',
			'rght' => '191',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:03:59',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:03:59',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '87',
			'name' => 'Hadar',
			'description' => 'A large city near the middle of Minteret. Though the soil there is cold, certain kinds of food grows there and nowhere else. ',
			'parent_id' => '81',
			'lft' => '156',
			'rght' => '157',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:19:24',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:19:24',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '88',
			'name' => 'Fabia',
			'description' => 'A fortress city right on the northern border. Passing through Fabia and over its north bridge takes one into Sirinuirnon. Fabia is filled with rich jewellers who obtain their materials from the towns far to the south. ',
			'parent_id' => '81',
			'lft' => '158',
			'rght' => '159',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:32:39',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:53:48',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '89',
			'name' => 'Gejeret',
			'description' => 'A small city similar to Hadar in that they farm rare foods in the soil there. ',
			'parent_id' => '81',
			'lft' => '160',
			'rght' => '161',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:34:05',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:34:05',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '90',
			'name' => 'Grenkeep',
			'description' => 'A small city near the Sideways Mountains. Rapturian Elemeniah rebelled against the dominant religion here but he eventually killed himself. Grenkeep now lies in ruins. ',
			'parent_id' => '81',
			'lft' => '162',
			'rght' => '163',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:36:14',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:36:14',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '91',
			'name' => 'Varoicca',
			'description' => 'An extravagent seaside city. The governing family here is extremely wealthy thanks to the mining guilds they own far to the west. It also acts as the primary port for law-abiders to travel eastward, until Sirantiryl\'s port, which is used mainly by outlaws. ',
			'parent_id' => '83',
			'lft' => '174',
			'rght' => '175',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:38:10',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:44:07',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '92',
			'name' => 'Banak',
			'description' => 'A city on the Banak Bay. Like Varoicca, rich families here own mining guilds to the west. Banak has many blacksmiths and goldsmiths. ',
			'parent_id' => '83',
			'lft' => '176',
			'rght' => '177',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:40:31',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:40:31',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '93',
			'name' => 'Thatra',
			'description' => 'A small city beside the Vastin Forest. Lumberjacks there fell some of the largest trees in Riiga to export. ',
			'parent_id' => '83',
			'lft' => '178',
			'rght' => '179',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:41:53',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:41:53',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '94',
			'name' => 'Tamenra',
			'description' => 'A small city on the southeastern shore of Taroiccin. Tamenra is known for its families of fortune tellers. ',
			'parent_id' => '83',
			'lft' => '180',
			'rght' => '181',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:43:10',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:43:10',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '95',
			'name' => 'Sirantyril',
			'description' => 'A city overrun with outlaws. As it acts as a central mining city for all of Velenaia, bandits from Sirantiryl often try to intercept the caravans of resources trying to reach Varoicca or Fabia. It also acts as the largest port for outlaws who wish to sail eastward. ',
			'parent_id' => '82',
			'lft' => '166',
			'rght' => '167',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:46:25',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:46:25',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '96',
			'name' => 'Vastin Forest',
			'description' => 'A large, dark, cold forest filled with Gruitin. Only the bravest lumberjacks enter here in groups to fell the massive trees, armed with suitable weapons. ',
			'parent_id' => '83',
			'lft' => '182',
			'rght' => '183',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:48:17',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:48:17',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '97',
			'name' => 'Hluff',
			'description' => 'The only known place where Sirins live. Hluff was built on a great hill, thought to be all that is left of the Trueblood\'s glorious city which once shimmered in the snow before humans drove the Truebloods away. ',
			'parent_id' => '84',
			'lft' => '186',
			'rght' => '187',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:50:27',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:50:27',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '98',
			'name' => 'Silian Island',
			'description' => 'A bitter cold island north of Ellecil, and only reachable via the ports there, if the ice has withdrawn to the north. Silian Island is known as a place so sacred that humans may not go there. ',
			'parent_id' => '10',
			'lft' => '193',
			'rght' => '194',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:51:58',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:51:58',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '99',
			'name' => 'Berinm',
			'description' => 'A small city on the western shore of Banak Bay. It is a popular mining place. ',
			'parent_id' => '82',
			'lft' => '168',
			'rght' => '169',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:53:23',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:53:23',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '100',
			'name' => 'Temenkajet',
			'description' => 'A small mining city against the northwest border of Velenaia. ',
			'parent_id' => '82',
			'lft' => '170',
			'rght' => '171',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:55:26',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 08:55:26',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '101',
			'name' => 'Idavio Islands',
			'description' => 'Two large islands between Tekrikri and Ketrem. ',
			'parent_id' => '1',
			'lft' => '196',
			'rght' => '203',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 08:57:47',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:21:45',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '102',
			'name' => 'Idavio King',
			'description' => 'An island holding the massive, ancient prison fortress of Mentiritis. It was once run by Idavio and his men, but has since fallen out of use. ',
			'parent_id' => '101',
			'lft' => '197',
			'rght' => '200',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:00:05',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 09:00:05',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '103',
			'name' => 'Mentiritis',
			'description' => 'An unbelievably large prison fortress, built ages before the first humans. It was discovered and used by Gabriel Idavio and his men but it fell out of use because it was too powerful. Gabriel took its key to Idavio Queen island. ',
			'parent_id' => '102',
			'lft' => '198',
			'rght' => '199',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:02:07',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 09:02:07',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '104',
			'name' => 'Idavio Queen',
			'description' => 'A barren island covered in sand and trees. Gabriel Idavio was said to have taken the key to Mentiritis to Idavio Queen to bury it so that it could never be found. ',
			'parent_id' => '101',
			'lft' => '201',
			'rght' => '202',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:03:03',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 09:03:03',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '105',
			'name' => 'Jindiara',
			'description' => 'A large country mixed with tropical jungles and cold mountains. Keid and Fanorans are found here, and both races are constantly at war with one another. ',
			'parent_id' => '2',
			'lft' => '320',
			'rght' => '337',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:47:02',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:23:03',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '106',
			'name' => 'Great Greens',
			'description' => 'The jungles of Jindiara, boasting two enormous lakes and several mountain ranges. Keid live all through the forests in what could be considered town and cities. The fortress wall of Daarbang separates the jungle from Fesinion. Though Keid do not mind visiting humans, the jungle itself and lurking Fanorans are often lethal. ',
			'parent_id' => '105',
			'lft' => '321',
			'rght' => '332',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:49:36',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 09:49:36',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '107',
			'name' => 'Fesinion',
			'description' => 'A vast region filled with coniferous mountains. Though no races live here, strange and foreign kinds of animals prove to be quite dangerous to even experienced explorers. The only way into the Red Peaks is through Fesinion. ',
			'parent_id' => '105',
			'lft' => '333',
			'rght' => '334',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:51:45',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 09:51:45',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '108',
			'name' => 'Red Peaks',
			'description' => 'The tall, sharp, cold mountains where Fanorans live. Extremely little is known about Fanorans; they kill all who try to enter their region. ',
			'parent_id' => '105',
			'lft' => '335',
			'rght' => '336',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:52:40',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 09:52:40',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '109',
			'name' => 'Shuptalxia',
			'description' => 'The Keiden capital. Buroba lives here in the temple of Genxren, along with a massive number of Keid. The city is the only place built by Keid, besides Daarbang, to be partly made of stone. ',
			'parent_id' => '106',
			'lft' => '322',
			'rght' => '323',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:55:13',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 09:55:13',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '110',
			'name' => 'Daarbang',
			'description' => 'The great wall of stone which cuts access between the Great Greens and Fesinion. Passage is only allowed through a single gate. Due to stories of hauntings and a lack of manpower, the Keid no longer man this fortress and it has fallen into ruin. ',
			'parent_id' => '106',
			'lft' => '324',
			'rght' => '325',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:56:35',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 09:56:35',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '111',
			'name' => 'Ankxarl',
			'description' => 'Normally the first Keiden place which humans visit because Ankxarl is nearest to the sea. It is a small city made mostly of wood, and since it is furthest from the Fanorans, they spend time building things for other Keid in need. ',
			'parent_id' => '106',
			'lft' => '326',
			'rght' => '327',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:58:16',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 09:58:16',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '112',
			'name' => 'Pzentelka',
			'description' => 'A small city by a large lake which is surrounded by high walls. It also has a small wooden fortress which acts as a safety point in case Shuptalxia becomes compromised. ',
			'parent_id' => '106',
			'lft' => '328',
			'rght' => '329',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 09:59:38',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 09:59:38',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '113',
			'name' => 'Emuxutalfa',
			'description' => 'The forefront of the battle between the Keid and the Fanorans. Emuxutalfa is a fortress city which tries to intercept any Fanorans who are prowling through the Great Greens. ',
			'parent_id' => '106',
			'lft' => '330',
			'rght' => '331',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 10:00:31',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 10:00:31',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '114',
			'name' => 'Iyakel',
			'description' => 'A large jungle island in the middle of the Ambelia Ocean where Hamakro live. It is normally avoided since no outsiders are welcomed there. ',
			'parent_id' => '2',
			'lft' => '338',
			'rght' => '341',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 10:02:59',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:23:30',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '115',
			'name' => 'Alakeleria',
			'description' => 'The jungles of Iyakel, inhabited by Hamakro weretigers. They dominate the jungle and do not allow anybody else to enter. ',
			'parent_id' => '114',
			'lft' => '339',
			'rght' => '340',
			'created' => '2010-08-02 10:03:42',
			'modified' => '2010-08-02 10:03:42',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '116',
			'name' => 'Curin',
			'description' => 'A large, cold island newly claimed by The Guards. Its southern end is teeming with monster-filled mountains. With its abundance of resources, Curin is considered to be a kind of new frontier, and many aspiring people are sent there. ',
			'parent_id' => '2',
			'lft' => '342',
			'rght' => '351',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 07:51:42',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:26:44',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '117',
			'name' => 'Fort Ralzain',
			'description' => 'The centerpiece of Curin is the mighty fortress of Ralzain. From here, the captain supervises all the construction on the small country. Though people here are hopeful, the cold weather and rugged terrain attack morale constantly. ',
			'parent_id' => '116',
			'lft' => '343',
			'rght' => '344',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 07:53:28',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 07:53:28',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '118',
			'name' => 'Nhetal',
			'description' => 'The largest port on Curin. Nhetal is where the people connect with South Ideitess, who reluctantly trade resources. ',
			'parent_id' => '116',
			'lft' => '345',
			'rght' => '346',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 07:54:34',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 07:54:34',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '119',
			'name' => 'Telmeth',
			'description' => 'The largest mining city on Curin, though somewhat small, is lucky enough to be situated by the water too. From here, people can sail into Pestaria\'s Cove and into the Ambelia Ocean. ',
			'parent_id' => '116',
			'lft' => '347',
			'rght' => '348',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 07:55:57',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 07:55:57',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '120',
			'name' => 'Folang Wood',
			'description' => 'A mysterious and mountainous wooded region, and in fact the most southern forest in Riiga. As the name implies, it has one of the largest Folang populations of any forest in Riiga. ',
			'parent_id' => '116',
			'lft' => '349',
			'rght' => '350',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 07:57:29',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 07:57:29',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '121',
			'name' => 'Evealdinn',
			'description' => 'A large, icy island to the north. Only stupidly brave adventurers here, as undiscovered monsters are said to dwell in the cold. ',
			'parent_id' => '2',
			'lft' => '352',
			'rght' => '355',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 07:59:24',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:24:24',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '122',
			'name' => 'Volass',
			'description' => 'One of the few temples known by humans. Volass is guarded by Srafel Duom and its entrance is not known. Many hunters travel to this extremely remote location with arranged game for sport hunting. ',
			'parent_id' => '121',
			'lft' => '353',
			'rght' => '354',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:01:16',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:01:16',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '123',
			'name' => 'North Ideitess',
			'description' => 'A country of fields surrounding a great lake. This kingdom is ruled by Kind Cyril, in Venzet. North Ideitess suffers at the hands of monsters who constantly try to come from the south. Carson\'s Wall protects the whole country from ambush. ',
			'parent_id' => '2',
			'lft' => '206',
			'rght' => '269',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:04:42',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:22:19',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '124',
			'name' => 'South Ideitess',
			'description' => 'One of the less glorious countries of Riiga. It is ruled by Emperor Voldagen who uses threats to control his people. The northern half is barren, but its southern half is lush with cold forests and majestic mountains. It does not have official provinces; it is divided into approximate geographical regions. ',
			'parent_id' => '2',
			'lft' => '270',
			'rght' => '319',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:06:18',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:22:31',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '125',
			'name' => 'Central Ideitess',
			'description' => 'The most dangerous place to set foot. The only known way into here is to pass through Carson\'s Wall in North Ideitess. ',
			'parent_id' => '2',
			'lft' => '356',
			'rght' => '359',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:07:03',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:24:41',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '126',
			'name' => 'Engis Valley',
			'description' => 'A winding, high, dangerous path along a seaside cliff face which leads into Central Ideitess. One wrong step can send the greatest hero tumbling to his or her death. ',
			'parent_id' => '125',
			'lft' => '357',
			'rght' => '358',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:08:17',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:08:17',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '127',
			'name' => 'Remdore',
			'description' => 'The primary province of North Ideitess. Its borders reach over into the Great Red Mountains. Within Remdore is the capital city of Venzet, where King Cyril reigns from. ',
			'parent_id' => '123',
			'lft' => '207',
			'rght' => '222',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:18:46',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:18:46',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '128',
			'name' => 'Karbak',
			'description' => 'The southwestern province of North Ideitess. Karbak is where the first Ideitens originally tried to settle, but they were too unused to the environment and had to sail north to Remdore to find somewhere with more resources and less nortu. ',
			'parent_id' => '123',
			'lft' => '223',
			'rght' => '238',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:19:55',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:19:55',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '129',
			'name' => 'Umberien',
			'description' => 'North Ideitess\'s northeastern province. Umberien, like the rest of the country, is mostly fields surrounded by mountains. The northern edge of Umberien marks entry into Sheberond Forest. ',
			'parent_id' => '123',
			'lft' => '239',
			'rght' => '252',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:21:42',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:21:42',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '130',
			'name' => 'Elginen',
			'description' => 'The southeastern mountainous province of North Ideitess. Carson\'s Wall is just south of its lower border. ',
			'parent_id' => '123',
			'lft' => '253',
			'rght' => '258',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:22:45',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:22:45',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '131',
			'name' => 'Remote Karbak',
			'description' => 'A province to the far west consisting mostly of mountains. Boasting very few towns, Remote Karbak is mostly uninhabited. ',
			'parent_id' => '123',
			'lft' => '259',
			'rght' => '262',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:23:41',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:23:41',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '132',
			'name' => 'Nilesiet',
			'description' => 'The far northern province of North Ideitess. Here, Nelesiens are found. They live near Avora, a remote temple in the deep snow to the north. ',
			'parent_id' => '123',
			'lft' => '263',
			'rght' => '268',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:25:34',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:25:34',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '133',
			'name' => 'Avora',
			'description' => 'One of the temples, found by the Nelesians and now used as their fortress. It\'s said that they hoard treasures within its mighty walls. ',
			'parent_id' => '132',
			'lft' => '264',
			'rght' => '265',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:26:51',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:26:51',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '134',
			'name' => 'Sheberond Forest',
			'description' => 'A large cold forest through which one must travel to reach Avora. It is filled with skilled Nelesian guards who often will kill and loot anybody on sight. It\'s considered madness to wander into here. ',
			'parent_id' => '132',
			'lft' => '266',
			'rght' => '267',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:28:43',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:28:43',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '135',
			'name' => 'VENZET',
			'description' => 'The capital of North Ideitess, boasting a mighty castle and a massive surrounding city. The castle has its back to the Great Red Mountains so that it may overlook all the land from up high. ',
			'parent_id' => '127',
			'lft' => '208',
			'rght' => '209',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:30:33',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:30:33',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '136',
			'name' => 'Harton',
			'description' => 'The first proper settling place of the first Ideitens. Harton is in a quiet, safe valley at the edge of the water. The Venzet River flows past it and into the sea as it always has done. ',
			'parent_id' => '127',
			'lft' => '210',
			'rght' => '211',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:32:00',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:32:00',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '137',
			'name' => 'Arsartia',
			'description' => 'A farming city surrounded by smaller cities. Arsartian stables boast some of the finest breeds of horses in North Ideitess. ',
			'parent_id' => '127',
			'lft' => '212',
			'rght' => '213',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:33:09',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:33:21',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '138',
			'name' => 'Amaiga',
			'description' => 'Once a glorious stone city, Amaiga is now the place of a vicious disease called Atramentous. It claims the lives of those unallowed to leave to prevent its spread, and has done so for thousands of years. Its only cathedral lies in ruins. ',
			'parent_id' => '127',
			'lft' => '214',
			'rght' => '215',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:35:38',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:10:15',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '139',
			'name' => 'Excil Vineyards',
			'description' => 'One of Remdore\'s famous vineyard cities which supplies the best wine to the rest of Riiga. ',
			'parent_id' => '127',
			'lft' => '216',
			'rght' => '217',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:37:36',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:37:36',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '140',
			'name' => 'Stratvai Vineyards',
			'description' => 'Another famous vineyard city, known as the place which supplied the lost mountain fortress of Veriheroth somewhere to the north. ',
			'parent_id' => '127',
			'lft' => '218',
			'rght' => '219',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:39:26',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:39:26',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '141',
			'name' => 'Norostan',
			'description' => 'A small mining city high in the East Karbak Mountains. The Venzet River flows past it. ',
			'parent_id' => '127',
			'lft' => '220',
			'rght' => '221',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:40:11',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:40:11',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '142',
			'name' => 'New Nelvi',
			'description' => 'A large city situated where Ideitens first tried to settle. Once overrun by nortu, it is now the place where nortu races are held in grand tournaments. New Nelvi also contains the largest cathedral in North Ideitess. ',
			'parent_id' => '128',
			'lft' => '224',
			'rght' => '225',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:43:20',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:10:50',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '143',
			'name' => 'Farfazen',
			'description' => 'A city on the shores of Lake Ideitess. On the other side of the city, the river Marakos flows. Farfazen is the place where Sage Nicolas Carson died. ',
			'parent_id' => '128',
			'lft' => '226',
			'rght' => '227',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:45:38',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:45:38',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '144',
			'name' => 'Gundaeyn Bay',
			'description' => 'A busy port city near New Nelvi. While its larger brother handles most of the trading ships, Gundaeyn Bay\'s ports deal mostly with fishermen. ',
			'parent_id' => '128',
			'lft' => '228',
			'rght' => '229',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:46:35',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:46:35',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '145',
			'name' => 'Oxwik Vineyards',
			'description' => 'A small vineyard city known for growing the best blue grapes. ',
			'parent_id' => '128',
			'lft' => '230',
			'rght' => '231',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 08:47:27',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 08:47:27',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '146',
			'name' => 'Amston',
			'description' => 'A small city north of New Nelvi where the largest nortu stations are found. ',
			'parent_id' => '128',
			'lft' => '232',
			'rght' => '233',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:01:21',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:01:21',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '147',
			'name' => 'Koskara',
			'description' => 'The last city anybody sees before they venture southward into Central Ideitess via Carson\'s Wall. ',
			'parent_id' => '128',
			'lft' => '234',
			'rght' => '235',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:02:40',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:02:40',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '148',
			'name' => 'Carson\'s Wall',
			'description' => 'Though technically outside the borders of Karbak, Carson\'s Wall is North Ideitess\'s primary and first defence against the hordes of The Enemy. ',
			'parent_id' => '128',
			'lft' => '236',
			'rght' => '237',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:04:50',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:04:50',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '149',
			'name' => 'Deilry',
			'description' => 'The largest city on Lake Ideitess. Deilry is popular with fishing and markets from all over Ideitess. It also boasts an impressive fortress overlooking the city and lake. ',
			'parent_id' => '129',
			'lft' => '240',
			'rght' => '241',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:05:59',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:05:59',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '150',
			'name' => 'Sonrill',
			'description' => 'The only decent eastern port in North Ideitess. Sonrill is where traders and travellers from the east arrive. As such, it is upheld as a beautiful and welcoming city. ',
			'parent_id' => '129',
			'lft' => '242',
			'rght' => '243',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:07:05',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:07:05',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '151',
			'name' => 'Fort Shefich ',
			'description' => 'A large fortress city on Lake Ideitess. It is one of the oldest active forts in the country. ',
			'parent_id' => '129',
			'lft' => '244',
			'rght' => '245',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:08:21',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:08:21',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '152',
			'name' => 'Lihuil',
			'description' => 'A cold and small mountain city near the western border. Aside from it being the place of birth and death of Tobias Edgard, and its grand cathedral, it is a quiet and humble place.',
			'parent_id' => '129',
			'lft' => '246',
			'rght' => '247',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:11:44',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:11:44',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '153',
			'name' => 'Ramston',
			'description' => 'A small fortified city on the fringe of the feared Sheberond Forest. Just north, up the road, is an outpost that tries to warn the country of any oncoming Nelesian invasions. ',
			'parent_id' => '129',
			'lft' => '248',
			'rght' => '249',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:12:52',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:12:52',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '154',
			'name' => 'Valkeven',
			'description' => 'A small farming city known for the best red grapevines in the country. ',
			'parent_id' => '129',
			'lft' => '250',
			'rght' => '251',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:14:05',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:14:05',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '155',
			'name' => 'Kristofen',
			'description' => 'A fortified mining city high in the Elgin Mountains. It has many of North Ideitess\'s most valuable mines. Only its high altitude and difficult terrain prevent it from growing larger. ',
			'parent_id' => '130',
			'lft' => '254',
			'rght' => '255',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:15:44',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:15:58',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '156',
			'name' => 'Vilenston',
			'description' => 'A small mining city northwest of Kristofen. It is the place where unique horns, called kristofa, are made. ',
			'parent_id' => '130',
			'lft' => '256',
			'rght' => '257',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:17:07',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:17:07',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '157',
			'name' => 'Sendilies',
			'description' => 'The only large town in Remote Karbak. It makes business from its mines. ',
			'parent_id' => '131',
			'lft' => '260',
			'rght' => '261',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:18:15',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:18:15',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '158',
			'name' => 'Silril Forest',
			'description' => 'The dense, lush forest of South Ideitess are pierced by mountains which support the grand temple and capital palace. The forest is kept in good condition as it acts as a defensive screen against oncoming forces. Guardian warriors of the Emperor swarm here in patrols. ',
			'parent_id' => '124',
			'lft' => '271',
			'rght' => '276',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:21:08',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:21:08',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '159',
			'name' => 'North Xilian',
			'description' => 'The vast, dry, rocky fields of North Xilian are filled with old cities and towns. Mountains to the east and west turn the region into a wind tunnel from the hot north winds or the chilling south winds, depending on the season. ',
			'parent_id' => '124',
			'lft' => '277',
			'rght' => '290',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:23:08',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:23:08',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '160',
			'name' => 'South Xilian',
			'description' => 'South Ideitess\'s primary shoreline region. Most foreign ships dock at the port cities here. It suffers arctic winds from the south almost constantly. ',
			'parent_id' => '124',
			'lft' => '291',
			'rght' => '302',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:24:16',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:24:16',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '161',
			'name' => 'West Xilian',
			'description' => 'Often known as the "suffering region"; the bridges crossing the Tumotora and Dranberan rivers are the only reasonable way to get there. If the emperor were to blockade these bridges, everybody in West Xilian would become cut off from the rest of the country. ',
			'parent_id' => '124',
			'lft' => '303',
			'rght' => '308',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:26:04',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:26:04',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '162',
			'name' => 'East Xilian',
			'description' => 'Known as the "safe region"; it is furthest from the emperor\'s palace, and so often gets away with being unnoticed. Most rebel factions originate from East Xilian. ',
			'parent_id' => '124',
			'lft' => '309',
			'rght' => '312',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:27:06',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:27:06',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '163',
			'name' => 'Xilian Canyons',
			'description' => 'Once lush and filled with life, since The Scouring in 5000BD, it has been a barren labyrinth of high canyons. The first Nelrens settled near the eastern shores here. ',
			'parent_id' => '124',
			'lft' => '313',
			'rght' => '318',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:30:37',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:30:37',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '164',
			'name' => 'Vyenri',
			'description' => 'The temple known to make Sage Nicolas Carson blind. It was ruined by humans just before The Scouring. Entry to its depths now seems to be impossible and what lies within is a mystery. Monsters are said to swarm here. ',
			'parent_id' => '163',
			'lft' => '314',
			'rght' => '315',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:32:08',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:32:08',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '165',
			'name' => 'Trelinia',
			'description' => 'Once the grandest city in Ideitess, Trelinia was begun by Nicolas Carson and in its center was the astounding Sun Tower which now stands at only half its height. Once the peak of human intelligence, the city was crushed by heavenly fire during The Scouring and has since remained empty. ',
			'parent_id' => '163',
			'lft' => '316',
			'rght' => '317',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:33:50',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:33:50',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '166',
			'name' => 'SILRIL',
			'description' => 'The capital palace of Emperor Voldagen. It is the first palace ever built by humans and, considering the surrounding steep forests and cliffs, it remains a grand sight to behold, despite its infamous ruler. ',
			'parent_id' => '158',
			'lft' => '272',
			'rght' => '273',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:36:10',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:36:10',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '167',
			'name' => 'Sefiunas',
			'description' => 'Though this grand forest-girt temple was once used by the first Nelrens, it now stands as a mere landmark, intentionally dwarfed by Silril Palace which stands on a higher hill nearby. The emperor does not allow entry. ',
			'parent_id' => '158',
			'lft' => '274',
			'rght' => '275',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:38:10',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:38:10',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '168',
			'name' => 'Nelvi',
			'description' => 'South Ideitess\'s oldest active city, Nelvi is where the Nelrens settled after The Scouring. Nelvi is dark, rundown, too big for its own good, and filled to the brim with outlaws. Though the emperor claims to run the Nelvi, many believe that king assassins bribe the emperor in order to hold the power here. ',
			'parent_id' => '159',
			'lft' => '278',
			'rght' => '279',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:41:13',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:41:13',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '169',
			'name' => 'Merlases',
			'description' => 'A city of bridges, tucked away on the other side of the Gazouna Mountains, northwest of Nelvi. Merlases is mainly a market city and its somewhat central location lends to this reputation. ',
			'parent_id' => '159',
			'lft' => '280',
			'rght' => '281',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:42:39',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:42:39',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '170',
			'name' => 'Kafecsil',
			'description' => 'A small farming city between Merlases and Nelvi. ',
			'parent_id' => '159',
			'lft' => '282',
			'rght' => '283',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:44:02',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:44:02',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '171',
			'name' => 'Espeil',
			'description' => 'A small mining city up in the Gazouna Mountains. It is situated high up the Espeil River. ',
			'parent_id' => '159',
			'lft' => '284',
			'rght' => '285',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:45:03',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:45:03',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '172',
			'name' => 'Hieril',
			'description' => 'The main easterly port for South Ideitess and also the location where Nelrens first settled. ',
			'parent_id' => '159',
			'lft' => '286',
			'rght' => '287',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:45:52',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:45:52',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '173',
			'name' => 'Ourtil',
			'description' => 'A small mining city in the Latilo Mountains. It supplies most of its materials to Silril Palace. ',
			'parent_id' => '159',
			'lft' => '288',
			'rght' => '289',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:46:51',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:46:51',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '174',
			'name' => 'Venugias',
			'description' => 'A port city on Ideitess\'s very southern shores. Venugias is mainly used for fishing and trade with places to the west. ',
			'parent_id' => '160',
			'lft' => '292',
			'rght' => '293',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:49:07',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:49:07',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '175',
			'name' => 'Solein',
			'description' => 'The most southerly city in South Ideitess. As such, it is very cold here. Its fishermen are said to rival those of Ellecil, in Huirnon, in terms of endurance. ',
			'parent_id' => '160',
			'lft' => '294',
			'rght' => '295',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:50:22',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:50:22',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '176',
			'name' => 'Finnusiare',
			'description' => 'A small farming city between mountains and forests. ',
			'parent_id' => '160',
			'lft' => '296',
			'rght' => '297',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:51:57',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:51:57',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '177',
			'name' => 'Eizey',
			'description' => 'A small port city north of Venugias. It is an old city, dating back to the discovery of Sefiunas. ',
			'parent_id' => '160',
			'lft' => '298',
			'rght' => '299',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:53:54',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:53:54',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '178',
			'name' => 'Ingis',
			'description' => 'A small city known for its families of skilled blacksmiths. ',
			'parent_id' => '160',
			'lft' => '300',
			'rght' => '301',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:55:50',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:55:50',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '179',
			'name' => 'Selesin',
			'description' => 'A small mining city hidden behind the Gazouna Mountains. It is home to numerous rebel factions who hold back the emperor\'s dominating touch. ',
			'parent_id' => '162',
			'lft' => '310',
			'rght' => '311',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:58:08',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:58:57',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '180',
			'name' => 'Saomi',
			'description' => 'A city deep in the Latilo Mountains bustling with quality mines. ',
			'parent_id' => '161',
			'lft' => '304',
			'rght' => '305',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 10:59:45',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 10:59:45',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '181',
			'name' => 'Clemiel',
			'description' => 'The most westerly place in South Ideitess. Clemiel is a small port city which is used to export Saomi\'s minerals. ',
			'parent_id' => '161',
			'lft' => '306',
			'rght' => '307',
			'created' => '2010-08-04 11:01:50',
			'modified' => '2010-08-04 11:01:50',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '182',
			'name' => 'North Nidonn',
			'description' => 'The grand country of the east. North Nidonn is highly religious, heavily populated, rich with resources, and ruled by the Phedailin Knights under King Enos and High Priestess Prinx Duos. ',
			'parent_id' => '3',
			'lft' => '362',
			'rght' => '453',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:15:23',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:24:58',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '183',
			'name' => 'South Nidonn',
			'description' => 'Southwest of the grand kingdom is an enormous desert inhabited by hostile Karithians. ',
			'parent_id' => '3',
			'lft' => '454',
			'rght' => '457',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:16:41',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:25:19',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '184',
			'name' => 'Estall Bay',
			'description' => 'A large ocean surrounded by two landmasses to the east and west. All three aspects are known as Estall Bay. Pirates roam these waters. Fort Shbel to the east battle the western pirates of Fort Pyhuana constantly. ',
			'parent_id' => '3',
			'lft' => '458',
			'rght' => '463',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:22:54',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:25:39',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '185',
			'name' => 'Yanuiri ',
			'description' => 'A heavily mountainous island known to be inhabited by werehusky Modeoa. They are so elusive and the terrain is so dangerous that almost nothing is known about them. ',
			'parent_id' => '3',
			'lft' => '464',
			'rght' => '467',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:23:52',
			'modified' => '2010-10-02 22:25:48',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '186',
			'name' => 'Phedailin',
			'description' => 'North Nidonn\'s most regal province, housing a temple of Hunnuklad and the royal palace. Nikina was first encountered by humans in this temple so the area is considered to be sacred. Thousands of generations of kings have ruled over these fields. ',
			'parent_id' => '182',
			'lft' => '363',
			'rght' => '380',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:26:20',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:27:53',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '187',
			'name' => 'Jevithem',
			'description' => 'The central province which joines the other four together. In the middle of Jevithem\'s rolling green plains is Lake Baymoor. It is the only province to boast two royal towers and it is also the largest province in Nidonn. ',
			'parent_id' => '182',
			'lft' => '381',
			'rght' => '398',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:27:42',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:27:42',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '188',
			'name' => 'Leotyne',
			'description' => 'The mountainous province of North Nidonn. Leotyne is heavily fortified and it has two great castles and a high fortress. Some of the walls built here are the tallest of anywhere in Riiga. ',
			'parent_id' => '182',
			'lft' => '399',
			'rght' => '412',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:29:11',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:29:11',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '189',
			'name' => 'Trelinia',
			'description' => 'Nidonn\'s forest province. Trelinia\'s sheltered woods and fields make it a cosy place to live. Astounding veins of gold mined in towns - not marked on any common map - have earned Trelinia the secondary title of the Golden Province. ',
			'parent_id' => '182',
			'lft' => '413',
			'rght' => '428',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:30:49',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:29:28',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '190',
			'name' => 'Laurondirin',
			'description' => 'A province consisting mostly of a red desert called the Simbea. The people here are quite a different race of human and are called Simbeans. Their fortresses and towers are red and they have many seaside towns. ',
			'parent_id' => '182',
			'lft' => '429',
			'rght' => '444',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:32:19',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:32:19',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '191',
			'name' => 'Old Belynsia',
			'description' => 'Once a powerful enemy of the king, Belynsia is now an empty field of grey dust and jagged mountains. Only three structures remain here and all of them are as feared as The Enemy. ',
			'parent_id' => '182',
			'lft' => '445',
			'rght' => '452',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:34:25',
			'modified' => '2010-08-08 01:15:14',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '192',
			'name' => 'DURACIA',
			'description' => 'The white capital of Nidonn. In its center is the royal palace - the largest manmade structure in Riiga - and Hunnuklad temple. Great walls protect the city and its distinct districts. ',
			'parent_id' => '186',
			'lft' => '364',
			'rght' => '367',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:39:31',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:39:31',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '193',
			'name' => 'Hunnuklad',
			'description' => 'Known to be the only place where Nikina will manifest in a visible form, Hunnuklad is an ancient temple now actively used by the Dualkedorian Order, ruled by the High Priestess Prinx Duos who consults with Nikina daily. A signed pass is required for entry. ',
			'parent_id' => '192',
			'lft' => '365',
			'rght' => '366',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:41:29',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:41:29',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '194',
			'name' => 'Entaro Fields',
			'description' => 'A huge farming city which supplies most of Phedailin with food. Its farms have been going for countless years. It has become almost a ritual to pass through Entaro on the way to or from Duracia. ',
			'parent_id' => '186',
			'lft' => '370',
			'rght' => '371',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:44:28',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:44:28',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '195',
			'name' => 'Simown',
			'description' => 'A small mining city up the Royal River. Most of its minerals go straight to Duracia. ',
			'parent_id' => '186',
			'lft' => '372',
			'rght' => '373',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:45:23',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:45:23',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '196',
			'name' => 'Logitio',
			'description' => 'A small fortified city which guards the only alternate road to Duracia around Entaro Fields. ',
			'parent_id' => '186',
			'lft' => '374',
			'rght' => '375',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:46:02',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:46:02',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '197',
			'name' => 'Fort Shelrein',
			'description' => 'Phedailin\'s primary fortress, governed by a paladin. It keeps watch westward over South Nidonn, in case Karithian\'s approach. Azure Tower, just to the west, marks the furthest border of Phedailin, though no citizens are allowed past Shelrein. ',
			'parent_id' => '186',
			'lft' => '368',
			'rght' => '369',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:48:38',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:48:38',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '198',
			'name' => 'Deaterio',
			'description' => 'Phedailin\'s largest port, though only a small city in comparison with others. It is situated on the southern shores. ',
			'parent_id' => '186',
			'lft' => '376',
			'rght' => '377',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:49:38',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:49:38',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '199',
			'name' => 'Whitap',
			'description' => 'A small mining city east of Duracia. Further east is the abandoned Fort Ramaun, and just beyond that is Old Belynsia. ',
			'parent_id' => '186',
			'lft' => '378',
			'rght' => '379',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 09:50:46',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 09:50:46',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '200',
			'name' => 'Vilenden',
			'description' => 'A large city on the Vilden River. Farmers here raise many kinds of livestock for food, working, and produce. ',
			'parent_id' => '187',
			'lft' => '386',
			'rght' => '387',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 10:30:41',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 10:30:41',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '201',
			'name' => 'Beryl Keep',
			'description' => 'Jevithem\'s primary fortress. It has one of the largest barracks in Nidonn and a large dock which enables trading across Lake Baymoor. ',
			'parent_id' => '187',
			'lft' => '384',
			'rght' => '385',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 10:35:11',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 10:35:11',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '202',
			'name' => 'Jevithem Castle',
			'description' => 'The home of Lord Tobias. Blue-grey, thick, dull, and filled with footsoldiers, it stands as a testimony to Jevithem\'s overbearing will. ',
			'parent_id' => '187',
			'lft' => '382',
			'rght' => '383',
			'created' => '2010-08-05 10:36:09',
			'modified' => '2010-08-05 10:36:09',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '203',
			'name' => 'South Riiga',
			'description' => 'Six large southerly land masses covered in icy peaks, snow, and frozen forests. It is inhabited only by Cullashin; only the stupidly adventurous travel here intentionally. ',
			'parent_id' => '',
			'lft' => '469',
			'rght' => '470',
			'created' => '2010-08-08 01:16:50',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:06:13',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '204',
			'name' => 'Cape Crossing',
			'description' => 'A large market city, popular for anybody going into Laurondirin. It often acts as Jevithem\'s second primary city as it lies directly across Lake Baymoor from the castle. Laurondirin\'s border once extended as far as Cape Crossing but Jevithem pushed the border back over the years. ',
			'parent_id' => '187',
			'lft' => '388',
			'rght' => '389',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:11:00',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:12:59',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '205',
			'name' => 'Maer',
			'description' => 'Jevithem\'s biggest port city on Lake Baymoor. It is a busy, centralised city. ',
			'parent_id' => '187',
			'lft' => '390',
			'rght' => '391',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:12:48',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:12:48',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '206',
			'name' => 'Cheriumn',
			'description' => 'A small city in Chera Forest. The first cathedral was built here and marks the center of the popular city. ',
			'parent_id' => '187',
			'lft' => '392',
			'rght' => '393',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:14:07',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:14:07',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '207',
			'name' => 'Cliffmere Farms',
			'description' => 'A small farming city right on the border next to Leotyne. Cliffmere used to be Leotian territory. ',
			'parent_id' => '187',
			'lft' => '394',
			'rght' => '395',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:15:06',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:15:06',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '208',
			'name' => 'Yele',
			'description' => 'A small city high in the mountains to the east. It\'s known to be the place where the current lord, Lord Lance, spent several years in hiding during Leotyne\'s period of corruption. ',
			'parent_id' => '187',
			'lft' => '396',
			'rght' => '397',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:16:36',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:16:36',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '209',
			'name' => 'Leotyne Castle',
			'description' => 'Arguably the most defensive fortification in the country, this castle overlooks all of Leotyne and sits atop a plateau reachable only via a winding and heavily guarded road. It is evidence of Leotyne\'s great defensive power. ',
			'parent_id' => '188',
			'lft' => '400',
			'rght' => '401',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:18:25',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:18:25',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '210',
			'name' => 'Fort Acadia',
			'description' => 'Fort Acadia and Fir Tower defend the road to Leotyne\'s small civil region. The only way around besides passing through the gate is to climb the sheer cliffs or to enter from the sea to the east. ',
			'parent_id' => '188',
			'lft' => '402',
			'rght' => '403',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:22:18',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:22:18',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '211',
			'name' => 'Landon',
			'description' => 'Leotyne\'s only city of decent size. Landon is situated across Landon Bridge which leads to Leotyne Castle. The city is fortified and often busy with traders and citizens. ',
			'parent_id' => '188',
			'lft' => '404',
			'rght' => '405',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:23:51',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:23:51',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '212',
			'name' => 'Teluel',
			'description' => 'A small city on the road to Fort Acadia. It is also a mining city and, like most Leotian cities, it is fortified with walls and towers. ',
			'parent_id' => '188',
			'lft' => '406',
			'rght' => '407',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:24:47',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:24:47',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '213',
			'name' => 'Highten',
			'description' => 'A small city between Landon and Fort Acadia. It consists primarily of mountain farmers. ',
			'parent_id' => '188',
			'lft' => '408',
			'rght' => '409',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:26:05',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:26:05',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '214',
			'name' => 'Sykratas',
			'description' => 'The only other way into Leotyne is to dock at the small port at Sykratas. Leotyne discourages use of this remote port; entry via Fort Acadia is strongly suggested. ',
			'parent_id' => '188',
			'lft' => '410',
			'rght' => '411',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:27:12',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:27:12',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '215',
			'name' => 'Trelinia Castle',
			'description' => 'This crowned castle, golden orange in the evening sun, is home to Lord Goldwin. The amount of gold in the province has sometimed earned its lords as having a greedy, secretive, or untrustworthy reputation. It is the only castle in Nidonn built next to the sea. ',
			'parent_id' => '189',
			'lft' => '414',
			'rght' => '415',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:40:47',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:40:47',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '216',
			'name' => 'Fort Arohed',
			'description' => 'Watching over the only valley entering Trelinia, Fort Arohed is the province\'s first defence. It has a moat - unusually - and also boasts a large archery range and barracks. ',
			'parent_id' => '189',
			'lft' => '416',
			'rght' => '417',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:44:02',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:44:02',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '217',
			'name' => 'Sedr Keep',
			'description' => 'Trelinia\'s second fortress is restricted to military access only. It is the place where Trelinia\'s best archers are trained and sometimes raised. It is deep in Woodridge, surrounded by high trees. ',
			'parent_id' => '189',
			'lft' => '418',
			'rght' => '419',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:45:29',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:45:29',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '218',
			'name' => 'Vesht',
			'description' => 'Trelinia\'s source for wood, and the city which is supposed to lead to the hidden mining towns in the western mountains. Vesht is Trelinia\'s most favoured city, though Nukvan is larger. It is also the birthplace of William Macelle. ',
			'parent_id' => '189',
			'lft' => '422',
			'rght' => '423',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:46:53',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:48:45',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '219',
			'name' => 'Nukvan',
			'description' => 'Trelinia\'s largest city. It is mostly farms and markets, and it is situated just north of Fort Arohed. ',
			'parent_id' => '189',
			'lft' => '420',
			'rght' => '421',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:48:24',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:48:24',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '220',
			'name' => 'Belynsia Mausoleum',
			'description' => 'A majestic tomb deep in Woodridge which holds all the recovered bodies from Katahedra\'s War. It is said that Sir William Macelle hid the spear Rushnukvan within the mausoleum, but to search for it would be an immense disrespect. ',
			'parent_id' => '189',
			'lft' => '424',
			'rght' => '425',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:52:33',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:52:33',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '221',
			'name' => 'Naekyn',
			'description' => 'A small farming city near the Yrth Range. There is a network of mines nearby, but they haven\'t been used in a long time. ',
			'parent_id' => '189',
			'lft' => '426',
			'rght' => '427',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 07:54:40',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 07:54:40',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '222',
			'name' => 'Laurondirin Castle',
			'description' => 'Laurondirin\'s architectural masterpiece. This castle has three rows of walls surrounding it. Within the center is a large stone keep, and within its great courtyard is another keep with four mighty towers. ',
			'parent_id' => '190',
			'lft' => '430',
			'rght' => '431',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:18:23',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:18:23',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '223',
			'name' => 'Ventet',
			'description' => 'Laurondirin\'s largest and most unique city is filled with magnificient stonework. Within it is Kaurden Stadium, the original and largest fistfighting stadium where all the tournaments are held. Rival fistfighting gangs sometimes cause trouble. ',
			'parent_id' => '190',
			'lft' => '432',
			'rght' => '433',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:23:03',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:23:03',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '224',
			'name' => 'Fort Brugend',
			'description' => 'Laurondirin\'s fortress is near the southern border and Crimson Tower is on the other side of the road. From there, one can see the entire cape valley which is the only way to reach Laurondirin on foot. ',
			'parent_id' => '190',
			'lft' => '434',
			'rght' => '435',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:24:19',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:24:19',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '225',
			'name' => 'Hanuan',
			'description' => 'A small port town, much safer than Port Lentrin. It is Laurondirin\'s primary port. ',
			'parent_id' => '190',
			'lft' => '436',
			'rght' => '437',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:25:28',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:25:28',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '226',
			'name' => 'Port Lentrin',
			'description' => 'Laurondirin\'s largest port city is close to pirate-infested waters, and so is heavily fortified. If the fishing there were not so outstanding, the city would not exist. ',
			'parent_id' => '190',
			'lft' => '442',
			'rght' => '443',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:26:26',
			'modified' => '2010-09-17 22:08:04',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '227',
			'name' => 'Mikneera',
			'description' => 'One of the province\'s small mining cities. It is near the Magno River, against the Heknian Mountains. ',
			'parent_id' => '190',
			'lft' => '438',
			'rght' => '439',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:27:15',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:27:15',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '228',
			'name' => 'Moruna',
			'description' => 'A small mining city known to be the place where the only piece of arkarum has ever been found. More Mines were subsequently dug into the earth to search for more but they were too ambitious and those mines collapsed and were sealed. ',
			'parent_id' => '190',
			'lft' => '440',
			'rght' => '441',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:28:41',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:28:41',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '229',
			'name' => 'Anukafobaia',
			'description' => 'Once the tallest structure ever witnessed by humans, Anukafobaia is now an immense ruin albeit only a fraction of the size it once was. It is said that Iethyer Gvoranshun hides deep in the forgotten dungeons here. ',
			'parent_id' => '191',
			'lft' => '446',
			'rght' => '447',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:31:20',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:35:22',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '230',
			'name' => 'Fort Tyriasa',
			'description' => 'Once a powerful fortress of the infamous Lord Katahedra, Fort Tyriasa is now a massive jumble of stones blocking entry to a cursed network of lost dungeons. ',
			'parent_id' => '191',
			'lft' => '448',
			'rght' => '449',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:32:36',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:32:36',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '231',
			'name' => 'Fort Ggehen',
			'description' => 'A ruined fortress far from Anukafobaia, Fort Ggehen is the target of brave adventurers. It is often the belief that, the further away something is from its ruler, the less formidable it is. This is certainly the assumption with this monstrous ruin. ',
			'parent_id' => '191',
			'lft' => '450',
			'rght' => '451',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:35:03',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:35:03',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '232',
			'name' => 'Kvoch Heric\'a',
			'description' => 'The largest desert on Riiga is inhabited by monstrous Karithians. The way to their fortresses and cities is not known, nor is it marked on any map or sign post. ',
			'parent_id' => '183',
			'lft' => '455',
			'rght' => '456',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:36:49',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:36:49',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '233',
			'name' => 'Merienis',
			'description' => 'A deep, dark, cold forest which is supposed to bring one into the valley within the God Peaks. Anybody can count the number of people who have returned from this Modeoa-inhabited valley with one finger. ',
			'parent_id' => '185',
			'lft' => '465',
			'rght' => '466',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:38:52',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:38:52',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '234',
			'name' => 'Hrash',
			'description' => 'The eastern jungle country of Estall Bay is inhabited by pirates claiming to suppress the tyranical forces coming from the western side. The way to Fort Shbel is known only to the pirates here. ',
			'parent_id' => '184',
			'lft' => '459',
			'rght' => '460',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:40:58',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:42:29',
		),
		array(
			'id' => '235',
			'name' => 'Burnia',
			'description' => 'The western country of Estall Bay is occupied by the pirates from Fort Pyhuana which is said to be overlooking a dark cove. Though pirates in general are feared, the pirates from Burnia are often referred to as demons. ',
			'parent_id' => '184',
			'lft' => '461',
			'rght' => '462',
			'created' => '2010-08-09 08:42:19',
			'modified' => '2010-08-09 08:42:19',
		),
	);
}

